## Part 4: Mermaid Diagrams

Visual diagrams from text

---
template: content
---

## Mermaid Diagram Support (v2.0.0)

Create diagrams using Mermaid.js syntax with \`\`\`mermaid code fences.

**Supported Diagram Types:**
- Flowcharts, Sequence, Class, State
- Gantt, Pie, ER, Journey

Example: `graph TD` or `graph LR` for flowcharts

---
template: diagram
caption: Sequence diagram showing client-server interaction
---

## Sequence Diagram Example

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant S as Server
    participant D as Database

    C->>S: HTTP Request
    S->>D: Query Data
    D-->>S: Results
    S-->>C: HTTP Response
```

---
template: diagram
caption: Class hierarchy for the MDSlides domain model
---

## Class Diagram Example

```mermaid
classDiagram
    SlideDeck --> Slide
    Slide --> SlideId
    Slide --> Template
    Template --> SlotDefinition

    class Slide {
        +id: SlideId
        +templateName: String
        +slots: Map
    }
```

