## Part 5: Text & Formatting

Markdown formatting features

---
template: content
---

## Text Formatting

MDSlides supports standard Markdown formatting:

**Bold text** using `**bold**`

*Italic text* using `*italic*`

`Inline code` using backticks

**Links:** [MDSlides Docs](https://github.com/tjm/mdslides)

---
template: content
---

## Code Blocks with Syntax Highlighting

Display code with automatic syntax highlighting:

```scala
def renderSlides(input: Path): IO[Unit] =
  for
    deck <- parseMarkdown(input)
    validated <- validateDeck(deck)
    html <- renderHTML(validated, theme)
    _ <- writeOutput(html)
  yield ()
```

**Supports 100+ languages** via highlight.js (v1.3.0)

