## Part 10: Best Practices

Guidelines for effective presentations

---
template: content
notes:
  - "Emphasize keeping slides simple"
  - "Reference accessibility guidelines"
---

## Content Best Practices

Follow these guidelines for effective presentations:

**Content Constraints:**
- One main idea per slide
- Max 12 lines of body text
- Keep headings under 80 characters
- Max 150 words per slide

**Visuals:**
- Use diagrams to clarify concepts
- Include alt text for all images
- Choose high-contrast themes

---
template: content
---

## Technical Best Practices

**File Organization:**
```
my-presentation/
  slides.md
  images/
    diagram1.png
    diagram2.svg
  .mdslides/
    config.json
```

**Version Control:**
- Commit `.mdslides/config.json`
- Commit source markdown files
- Ignore `output/` directories

---
template: content
---

## Template Selection Guide

Choose the right template for each slide:

**title** - Opening slide, section covers
**content** - Default for most slides
**diagram** - When diagrams are the main focus
**section-title** - Major section transitions
**closing** - Thank you, contact info, Q&A

Use frontmatter to specify:
```yaml
---
template: diagram
caption: System architecture overview
---
```

